verbose_text: The levels of IL-6 (207.90 +/-16.69) and TNF-alpha (239.60 +/-15.27) in group M was significantly increased, compared with those in group N (85.93 +/-20.31 and 101.23 +/-11.91, respectively) (all P < 0.01); whereas there was no difference in the level of ICAM-1 between group N (1.44 +/-0.15) and group M (1.79 +/-0.35) (P> 0.05; XREF_FIG).
